lso shown to be relevant in ideological debates about hybrid or cross national literary production in the Arab milieu. Language ideology appears to be everywhere, including in discussions of the cognitive role of language in linking thought to reality, to which a whole chapter is devoted. Here, building on his highly acclaimed previous published works, Yasir Suleiman takes in a new direction his arguments on ideology and cultural politics."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aAnthropological linguisticszArab countries. 0aArabic languagexHistory. 0aArabic languagexSocial aspects. 0aLanguage and culturezArab countries. 0aSociolinguisticszArab countries. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748680320zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748680320423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748680320/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK